metadata.description:
Another day, another m211 mp3 release, and this time it's the mp3 debut of that funk soul brother Bay Tremore. He hits us with one of his intriguingly original drum and bass tracks - sorta somewhere towards the techstep that so dominates d+b nowadays but then shying away towards the melodic under-ratedness of artists such as Arcon2 or even Springheel Jack.

In fact, it's different again, and, much like the Tek tune we've previously put out on mp3, it offers a different perspective to a well-worn formula. Different perspectives, we're sure you'll agree, are good. And the ticktock-zooming-to-bass effect partway through the track is damn original to boot...
metadata.title: Bay Tremore - Four77 [mtw005]
